The DLL MSVCP71.dll is a run-time library that applications compiled 
with Visual C++ .NET need to run.   If you have Visual C++ .NET on your 
system, then you probably already have this DLL.  If not, you should be 
able to find it in the folder where you installed Cantera.  (It may not 
be obvious that it is there, since depending on your settings for this 
folder, Windows may hide it from you. )  You probably need to move it 
into the Windows system directory (e.g. C:&#92;WINDOWS&#92;SYSTEM32). I thought 
this would happen automatically, but maybe not.

Dave

